Nigeria is away to Lesotho in the second fixture of their 2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualifying series. It is the third time ever both countries will face each other on the international scene. The Super Eagles go into Sunday’s game top of Group L, following their 2-1 win over Benin Republic on Wednesday. The Crocodiles fought back to hold Sierra Leone to a 1-1 draw on Wednesday. Due to the termination of Lagardere’s media rights, the game will not be live on SuperSport. However, NTA is expected to beam the game. Kick off at the 20,000-capacity Setsoto Stadium in Maseru is 5pm West African time. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.